      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MINOS NZ (3) was beaten into fourth as favourite in his first outing for Jason Grimson at Menangle last start but he did have to work when racing parked and was only 3.4m off the winner. That was his first hitout for seven weeks and he has won a trial since so should have come one. Big chance from a good draw. SWEET ON LEXY (4) has been impressive since switching back to Brisbane, winning his last two outings by big margins. Takes a step up in grade but raced parked from a similar barrier to this last week and then drew right away to salute by more than 15m. Could well land the hat trick. BIRKIRKARA (9) made it three placings in a row when beaten a head last week. May need some luck from the back row but should be at peak fitness now and has the hoof on the till. OZZIE PUNTA (7) draws wide but was luckless last week so has some claims off his win here prior.",
